          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "Pearl index is defined as the number of failures per 100 woman years of exposure (HWY) Failure rate per Hundred Women Years = Total accidental pregnancies X 1200/ Total months of exposure Reference : Park&;s textbook of preventive and social medicine, 23rd edition, Page no: 510",
          "hint": "Topic: Demography and family planning"
