          "correctOptionId": "opt-2",
          "explanation": "Sentinel surveillance is a method for identifying the missing cases and thereby supplementing the notified cases. it estimates disease prevalence in the total population. Repoing biases are minimised. It detects missing cases; so it comes under secondary prevention. Ref : Park&;s Textbook of Preventive and Social Medicine; 23rd edition - Pgno 40",
          "hint": "Topic: Concept of health and disease"
