          "correctOptionId": "opt-1",
          "explanation": "The objectives of MCH care are-\n\nReduction of morbidity and mortality rates of mothers  and children \nPromotion of reproductive health\nPromotion of the physical and psychological development of child within family \n\nThis is achieved by working under the following sub components- \n\nMaternal health \nFamily planning\nChild health \nSchool health \nHandicapped children \nCare of children in special settings such as day care centres\n\nIt is evident from the objectives and Sub components that the most effective step is maternal health promotion .\nFactors that effect maternal health such as urbanisation , rural migration , changing patterns of women's work and status is seen to have direct effect on child bearing and child rearing. Thus by achieving maternal health,it is possible to assure the achievement of all other steps. Hence option 1 is the most appropriate answer."
