          "explanation": "Multiphasic screening: application of two or more screening tests in combination to a large number of people at one time. Example: annual health check ups. Multipurpose screening: screening by more than one test done simultaneously to detect more than one disease. Example: screening of a pregnant women for VDRL, HIV, HBV serological tests on a blood sample. Mass screening: Screening test applied on large population. Eg- CXR in elderly. High risk/ selective screening: Applied on high risk groups .Eg- screening for HIV in commercial sex workers.",
