          "explanation": "Ans. is 'd' i.e., Number of females per 1000 males Sex ratioo Sex ratio is defined as the number of females per 1000 males. Sex ratio is considered asi) Favourable: When females are more than males (> 1000 females per 1000 males),ii) Unfavourable: When females are less than males (< 1000 females per 1000 males),iii) Ideal: Females are equal in number as males (1000 females per 1000 males).o India has sex ratio 940 (It was 933 in 2001). Only two states/UT have favourable sex ratio : Kerala (highest sex ratio of 1084) and Puducherry. Dadra & Nagar Haveli has lowest sex ratio,o Child sex ratio is defined as females (0-6 years age) per 1000 males (0-6 years age). Child sex ratio of India has reached an all time low of 914 since 1961. The fall has been 13 points from 927 (in 2001) to 914 (in 2011). It is highest in Mizoram and lowest in Harayana.o Sex ratio at birth in India is 914.",
